            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-01-98 12:55 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Actually just to answer someones question. I am a big marvin the martian fan and there is actually a marvin the martian pez dispenser. It is not a real pez dispenser it's motorized. If you haven't seen it I can send you a pic. I do not have it because I have only seen it once for sale and that is today on eBay. If anyone knows where to get these I would gladly appreciate it.</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Pez Janitor</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-01-98 06:04 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">There has been speculation of a Marvin dispenser, not the motorized one. Although it hasn't been confirmed, it would be a nice addition to the Warner Bros. line.</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>pezjenny</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-01-98 08:27 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">re: motorized dispensers<br>
            I saw a Bugs Bunny one with Skittles today at the Mr. Bulky's store in the mall. they didn't have the Pez ones, but they said they expected to get them at some point. they look great in the e-bay pic; I look forward to getting them.</font>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">re: holiday variations in the states<br>
            I really hope this is true, but I expect that if they come they will not be much cheaper than currently available from dealers - the one newsletter said Pez thinks collectors will be pleased with the presentation (or something like this) but I believe they said that about the eyes too, and I felt those were overpriced. I don't know, I keep waffling on the holiday dispensers. I REALLY want them, but can't quite afford the price. I'm crossing my fingers for good Pez news though.</font></p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
