          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-08-98 09:44 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">There is a Marvin the Martian Motorized PEZ dispenser, there is also a Willie Coyote W/ Road Runner Dispenser. There might even be another one. I have a Marvin avaliable if anyone is interested. Also is there a new Wolverine dispenser?</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>sketch</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-16-98 12:38 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">There are only two motorized Pez handers. They are Marvin the Martian and Wile E. Coyote. I read somewhere that they had seen them at walmart for $5-$7. I don't know if they are in walmarts all over, but I hope so. I haven't gotten to walmart lately so I don't know if they have them there, but I have found a lot of Pez that aren't at other stores, so I'm hoping.</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>feldamundo</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 09-23-98 08:18 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">According to the latest Fliptop PEZervation Society newsletter, the new Warner Brothers dispensers will be a sports series. The newsletter says, "I haven't been told what characters will be included, but they will be getting baseball hats, sunglasses, etc. I have heard that Bugs, Taz, Sylvester, and possibly 1 other character are set for the change. They will be sold worldwide."</font>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">The projected release date for these, pending final approval, is Summer 1999.</font></p>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">There's also a new Easter Bunny coming out next spring. There's a picture of it at:<br>
            http://narrowgate.net/~fliptoppez/TFPSpage2.htm</font></p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Quietman</b></font></td>
